Evaluability	  says	  you	  should	  not	  be	  asserting	  anything	  that	  might	  be	  unevaluable.	  Non-­‐triviality	  says	  you	  should	  not	  be	  
asserting	  anything	  whose	  truth-­‐value	  is	  already	  settled.	  Unequivocality	  says	  that	  the	  content	  of	  your	  utterance	  should	  not	  
depend	  on	  possibly	  unknown	  facts.	  
	  
